arStrings.szText: (laughs) I'm sorry, friend. I know that joke was in poor taste, but laughing feels better than crying.
A small chuckle, a genuine reflection on the pain you experienced. Earnest. You told a poor joke to try to hide your pain, trying to smile through it.
I cannot thank you enough for rescuing me from that demon's trap. Seeing how many times I had...fallen prey to his lies...
Earnest. You were about to say "how many times i had died" but stop yourself and instead say "fallen prey".
My family, my father's memory. We are all free of Beleth's curse.
I want you to have my father's sword. I think it can do more good with you than with me. I think that's what he would have wanted.
Thank you again for everything. I won't ever forget you. Well, I won't ever forget you again.
emphasis on "again", as you've lost your memory of the player several times until now.
